<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure10>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Distribution of Novochares abbreviatus species group A N. abbreviatus: examined specimens (red) and literature / unconfirmed records (blue) B N. oculatus: examined specimens (red) and literature / unconfirmed records (blue) C N. pallipes (red), N. latus (yellow), N. baca (blue), N. pilatus (green)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881177" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure9>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Aedeagi and habitus of the Novochares abbreviatus species group A-E N. oculatus: A-C aedeagus, Mexico D, E paralectotype from Guatemala D aedeagus E habitus F-K miscellaneous forms of aedeagi in the Novochares abbreviatus species group F, G Argentina H, I Venezuela J, K Bolivia L, M, R N. pallipes N, O N. baca A, D, F, H, J, L, N dorsal view B, M ventral view C, G, I, K, O lateral view R oblique view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881176" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

